### 4. Media / Person / Podcast Details

```
POST /api/details
```

Get detailed information for a specific item or a batch of items.

#### Scalar lookup

```
POST /api/details?mc_id={id}&mc_type={type}
```

Returns a single JSON object. `source_id` is optional — derived from `mc_id` when absent.

#### Batch lookup

```
POST /api/details?mc_ids={id1},{id2},{id3}&mc_type={type}
```

Returns a JSON array (positional). Unresolved IDs appear as `null` at their index; the request itself returns HTTP 200.
Uses `JSON.MGET` (single Redis round-trip) for index-only types (person, podcast, author, book without `force`).

#### Parameters

| Param | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `mc_id` | one of `mc_id` / `mc_ids` | Single item identifier |
| `mc_ids` | one of `mc_id` / `mc_ids` | Comma-separated identifiers for batch |
| `mc_type` | yes | `movie`, `tv`, `person`, `podcast`, `book`, or `person` with `mc_subtype=author` |
| `source_id` | no | Upstream numeric ID; derived from `mc_id` when absent |
| `mc_subtype` | no | e.g. `author` for OpenLibrary authors |
| `force` | no (default `false`) | When `true`, fetch live upstream data (e.g. TMDB credits for person) |
| `rss_details` | no (default `false`) | When `true`, include RSS episodes for podcasts |
| `fields` | no | Comma-separated field names to return. `id`/`mc_id` always included. When omitted, all fields are returned. |

#### Field projection

When `fields` is provided, each result object is reduced to only the listed keys plus `id` and `mc_id` (always present). Applies to both scalar and batch responses. `null` entries in batch results remain `null`.

```
POST /api/details?mc_ids=tmdb_person_287,tmdb_person_1461&mc_type=person&fields=popularity,search_title
```

```json
[
  {"id": "tmdb_person_287", "search_title": "Brad Pitt", "popularity": 10.42},
  {"id": "tmdb_person_1461", "search_title": "George Clooney", "popularity": 5.34}
]
```

#### Behaviour by type

- **movie / tv**: Always enriches with live TMDB watch providers and cast.
- **person** (default): Returns Redis index document only. With `force=true`, supplements with live TMDB person details and movie/TV credits.
- **podcast**: Returns Redis index document. With `rss_details=true`, includes RSS feed episodes.
- **author / book**: Returns Redis index document only.

